RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAPTAIN CREED broke outward and made contact with Fairpit then gave chase, rounded the turn about the three path, drifted into the lane but dug in and dueled LONG LEGS through later yards for the win. The latter set the pace inside, came under pressure approaching the quarter pole and contested the edge nearest the rail on the turn, was steadily handled leaving the turn but reluctantly ceded later yards. GOLDEN ADAGE was bumped at the break then gave chase, raced two deep on the turn then flattened toward mid-stretch. FAIRPIT was bumped outward and into Golden Adage leaving the gate and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: Captain Creed
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out,bumped,chased,3p turn,drifted,late duel for win

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GHOST OF ALCINA chased through the backstretch and raced close off the rail on the turn, was carried out leaving the turn but dug in for the lead mid-stretch and held on with steady encouragement. MISS ARGENTINA gave chase, rounded the turn about the three path, drifted leaving the turn but finished well to take second later yards and was gaining on the winner. CAJUN CASHEW drew clear and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure toward the quarter pole, raced at the rail on the turn but drifted into the lane, was met toward mid-stretch and flattened the final sixteenth. LIL SPITTIN IMAGE chased outside, raced near the rail on the turn and weakened. VERITAS LUX MEA came away a step slow and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: Ghost of Alcina
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,close off rail turn,carried out 1/8,up 1/16,held on drving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Allowance Purse 27400. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 23 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 23 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Whe re Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POLISH THE DIAMOND rated the pace inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and was steadily handled to hold on well. LA MADDALENA steadied into the first turn and raced in the five path through the turn, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path, flattened in the stretch and settled for second. IHEARTRAINACOMN settled in the three path the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the four path and came along for third inside the sixteenth pole. JUMPIN JACK BRASS saved ground, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn then flattened in the lane. PHILMARY CASTLE rounded the first turn about the six path, left the turn outside and picked up the chase past the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the six path on the far turn and showed little more. LAUGHINTOTHEBANK saved ground on the opening turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole but showed little response. LUZIA stalked off the rail on the opening turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn. SCARLET REBEL rounded the first turn about the four path, gave chase toward the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and weakened in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Luzia
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked off rail,chased 3/8,weakened rail far turn

ENTRY.NAME: Polish the Diamond
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated pace inside,pressured 3/8,rail turn,held well driving
